	 public static String  imp_Msg_Header="IMPORTANT:";
	 
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line01="•  For details, rules and terms & conditions of E-Ticketing services, please visit www.irctc.co.in.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line02="•  Departure time and Arrival Time printed on this ERS and VRM sent through mail are liable to change. Please check correct departure, arrival from \n    Railway Station Enquiry, Dial 139 or SMS RAIL to 139.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line03="•  There are amendments in certain provision of Refund Rules. Refer Amended Refund Rules w.e.f. 12-Nov-2015. (Details available on www.irctc.co.in under \n    heading Refund Rules at the bottom)";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line04="•  The accommodation booked is not transferable and is valid only if the ORIGINAL ID card prescribed is presented during the journey. The SMS/ERS \n    along with valid ID card of any one the passenger booked on e-ticket proof in original would be verified by TTE with the name and PNR on the chart. \n    If the Passenger fail to produced/display SMS/ERS due to any eventuality(loss, damaged mobile/laptop etc.) but has the prescribed original proof of \n    identity, a penalty of Rs.50/- per ticket as applicable to such cases will be levied. The ticket checking staff on board/off board will give excess fare ticket \n    for the same.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line05="•  E-ticket cancellations are permitted through www.irctc.co.in by the user.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line06="•  PNRs having fully waitlisted status will be dropped and the names of the passengers on such tickets will not appear on the chart. They are not allowed to \n    board the train. However the names of PARTIALLY waitlisted/confirmed and RAC ticket passenger will appear in the chart.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line07="•  Obtain certificate from the TTE /Conductor in case of (a) PARTIALLY waitlisted e-ticket when LESS NO. OF PASSENGERS travel, (b) A.C.FAILURE, \n    (c) TRAVEL IN LOWER CLASS. This original certificate must be sent to GGM (IT), IRCTC, Internet Ticketing Centre,  2nd Floor, Tower-D \n    World Trade Centre, Nauroji Nagar, New Delhi-110029, after filing TDR online within prescribed time for claiming refund.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line08="•  In case of Partial confirmed/RAC/Wait listed ticket, TDR should be filed online within prescribed time in case NO PASSENGER is travelling \n    for processing of refund as per Railway refund rules.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line09="•  Confirmed ticket can be cancelled up to thirty minutes before scheduled departure of the train. However, no refund shall be granted on cancellation of \n    confirmed ticket after four hours before the scheduled departure of train.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line10="•  RAC/partially confirmed Ticket can be cancelled up to thirty minutes before scheduled departure of the train. However, refund will be granted as per \n    provisions of extant Railway Refund Rule.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line11="•  In case of Train Cancellation on its entire run, full refund will be granted automatically by the System. However, if the train is cancelled partially on \n    its run, passengers are required to file TDR within 72hrs from schedule departure of the train from the passenger's boarding station.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line12="•  Passengers are advised not to carry inflammable/dangerous/explosive/articles as part of their luggage and also to desist from smoking in the trains.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line13="•  Contact us on: - 24*7 Hrs Customer Support at 0755-6610661, 0755-4090600 or Mail To: care@irctc.co.in.";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line14="•  Variety of meals available in more than 1500 trains. For delivery of meal of your choice on your seat log on to www.ecatering.irctc.co.in or call 1323 \n    Toll Free. For any suggestions/complaints related to Catering services, contact Toll Free No. 1800-111-321 (07.00 hrs to 22.00 hrs)";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line15="•  FOR MEDICAL EMERGENCY/FIRST AID, CONTACT TICKET CHECKING STAFF/GUARD OR DIAL 138.(ALL India Passenger Helpline No. 138)";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line16="•  PNR and train arrival/departure enquiry no. 139";
	 public static String  imp_Msg_Line17="•  To report unsavory situation during journey, Please dial railway security helpline no. 182";
	 
	 
