	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC="c)   Cancellation and refund rules :";


	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC01="     1.  Confirmed E-ticket before chart preparation: E-ticket can be cancelled online and the amount will be refunded electronically to the respective agent's account used for booking.";
	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC02="     2.  Confirmed E-ticket after chart preparation: Cancellation/ refund request received after preparation of chart are forwarded by IRCTC to concerned railway for manual processing. \n          Refund amount received from concerned railway will be credited back to the respective agent's account used for booking by IRCTC.";
	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC03="     3.  Partially waitlisted E-ticket before chart preparation: E-ticket can be cancelled online and the amount will be refunded electronically to the respective agent's account used for booking.";
	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC04="     4.  Partially waitlisted E-ticket after chart preparation: E-ticket cannot be cancelled online after chart preparation. Partially waitlisted e-ticket holder where part passengers have travelled and want to\n          claim refund for passengers who have not travelled is required to send the original certificate issued by TTE / Conductor in lieu of the same to IRCTC after filing online refund request through the \n          respective agent. The partially waitlisted e-ticket holder where no passengers have travelled and wants to claim refund is required to file online refund request through the respective agent. It would \n          then be forwarded to concerned railway and refund received from Railways would be credited back electronically to the respective agent's account used for booking by IRCTC.";
	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingC05="     5.  If the ticket is partially waitlisted/ Confirmed/ RAC at remote location chart preparation then E-ticket cannot be cancelled online. It is required to file refund request online for claiming refund \n          through the respective agent. It would then be processed offline and refund received from Railways would be credited back electronically the respective agent's account used for booking by IRCTC.";

	 public static String  sp_Block03_HeadingD="d)   Dynamic fare pricing :";
	 
